    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="586"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.516/32.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Blanchard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 31, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You are instructed to protest to the Haitian authorities against any interference
                    with the Bank of Haiti in view of the fact that it is owned and operated by
                    Americans and other foreigners. In case the bank is forced to close and cease
                    operations by the present Haitian Government, this Government will not recognize
                    any forfeiture of the charter of the bank resulting from such enforced closure.
                    You may add that this Government is deeply concerned over the reports which have
                    reached it as to the arbitrary conduct of the authorities in dealing with
                    foreign interests in the Republic.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
